en_374340_0	Travel publisher Lonely Planet says Sri Lanka is continuing to be the top destination for 2019 despite the Easter Sunday terror attacks.
en_374340_1	The travel publication, one of the most popular in the world, maintained Sri Lanka as number one, while warning readers to check travel advisories of their governments before travelling to the island nation.
en_374340_2	The publication says Sri Lanka deserves the top spot for its food, ‘epic train rides’, and scenic hills and beaches.
en_374340_3	Tourist arrivals to Sri Lanka fell 70 percent in May, amidst foreign governments warning against travel to Sri Lanka.  Most such advisories have now been relaxed.
en_374340_4	Germany and Zimbabwe are ranked second and third among the top 10 countries to travel this year.
en_374340_5	This has been a huge victory for Sri Lanka, three months after the Easter attack.
en_374340_6	Economic analysts point out that the government’s concession to the tourism industry and strong security measures have also directly impacted to achieve the result.
en_374340_7	Meanwhile, there has been a significant increase in the number of tourist arrivals to the island in recent weeks.
en_374340_8	Our correspondents say tourists flock to historical sites such as Anuradhapura, Polonnaruwa and Sigiriya.
